SUMMARY:Wilderness Union Adventure Trivia
DESCRIPTION:Wilderness Union Toronto - Outdoor Adventure and Hiking Club\n
 **Please note the only way to register for this adventure is on [our websi
 te.](https://www.wildernessunion.com/adventures/adventure-trivia)**\n\nWe'
 ve teamed up with the legendary Quizmaster Jess team and MEC to bring you 
 a night dedicated entirely to the backcountry. Expect a room full of peopl
 e who would rather be in a tent than a cubicle\, battling it out over surv
 ival stories\, epic expeditions\, and gear knowledge.\n\n**Why You Should 
 Be There:**\n**\\- The Prize\\.** We've got 3 prize packs of **premium out
 door gear worth over $400** to give away courtesy of MEC.\n**\\- The Commu
 nity\\.** You'll get to meet a crew who have big plans to explore this sum
 mer.\n**\\- The Hosting\\.** Analisa from the Quizmaster Jess team is at t
 he helm\, bringing seven years of expertise to ensure the night is filled 
 with banter\, curveballs\, and great energy.\n\n**What to Expect**\n**High
 -Stakes Competition.** Multiple rounds of nature-adjacent trivia spanning 
 roughly two hours of gameplay.\n**Solo-Friendly Setup.** We specialize in 
 matching solo adventurers with friendly teams because the best stories usu
 ally start with meeting a stranger.\n‍**Great Food and Drinks.** Saint J
 ohn’s Tavern offers a full pub menu and a wide selection of drinks avail
 able at your table throughout the entire evening.\n\n**Highlights**\nMEC P
 rizes. Quizmaster Jess Team. Meet the Crew.\n\n**Event cost: from $5 + HST
  - optional transport available.**\n**Register [here.](https://www.wildern
 essunion.com/adventures/adventure-trivia)**\n\n**About Wilderness Union**\
 nWilderness Union is deliberate about building an outdoors community that 
 connects you to the life-changing magic of the outdoors and helps you find
  your people.\n\nMembers range from 20-40 years old. The group is a mix of
  GTA locals and newcomers to Toronto from within Canada and abroad.\n\nAtt
 endance numbers on Meetup don't reflect our actual event attendance - we t
 ypically have 15-20 community members at each event. Large enough that the
 re's someone new to meet but small enough that it's not overwhelming!\n\n*
 **Learn more at our website [www.wildernessunion.com](https://www.wilderne
 ssunion.com/)***
