SUMMARY:Locating Limberlost - A Wilderness Hike
DESCRIPTION:Wilderness Union Toronto - Outdoor Adventure and Hiking Club\n
 **Please note the only way to register for this adventure is on [our websi
 te.](https://www.wildernessunion.com/adventures/locating-limberlost)**\n\n
 ***Join us for this 10km trek through the quiet\, stunning wilderness of M
 uskoka.***\nWe'll be exploring the edge of Algonquin Provincial Park in a 
 little-known spot with pristine lakes\, budding forests\, and incredible r
 ocky landscapes.\nAs we hike along the trail and trace the edge of a cryst
 al-clear lake\, you can expect:\n\n* Dense\, old-growth forests where towe
 ring trees create a dramatic canopy overhead\n* Ancient granite cliffs ris
 ing up from the shoreline\, carved by glaciers over millions of years.\n* 
 Possible glimpses of wildlife like deer\, beavers\, and all sorts of birds
  that call this place home.\n\nOne of the coolest parts of the hike is get
 ting to see the raw beauty of the Canadian Shield up close. We'll stop at 
 several lookout points where you can take in the incredible panoramic view
 s of the surrounding wilderness.\n\n**There's a mix of terrain\, including
  boardwalks\, rocky sections\, and well-maintained paths\, which is suitab
 le for any moderately fit hiker.**\n\n**Highlights**\n**Stunning Views -**
  Enjoy wild views of the iconic Canadian Shield at the many lookout points
  along this hike\n**Floating Boardwalk -** Stroll across a beautiful float
 ing boardwalk along the lake’s edge\n**Sprawling Forest Reserve -** With
  over 10\,000 acres and 70+ trails\, this hidden gem has so much to offer\
 n\n**Event cost: $60+HST - optional transport available.**\n**Register [he
 re.](https://www.wildernessunion.com/adventures/locating-limberlost)**\n\n
 **About Wilderness Union**\nWilderness Union is deliberate about building 
 an outdoors community that connects you to the life-changing magic of the 
 outdoors and helps you find your people.\n\nMembers range from 20-40 years
  old. The group is a mix of GTA locals and newcomers to Toronto from withi
 n Canada and abroad.\n\nAttendance numbers on Meetup don't reflect our act
 ual event attendance - we typically have 15-20 community members at each e
 vent. Large enough that there's someone new to meet but small enough that 
 it's not overwhelming!\n\n***Learn more at our website [www.wildernessunio
 n.com](https://www.wildernessunion.com/)***
